      "text": "# AEO Audit\n\nAudit blog posts and brand presence for Answer Engine Optimization — ensuring AI models accurately represent your brand and surface your content in AI-generated answers.\n\n## Why AEO Matters\n\nAI answer engines (ChatGPT, Perplexity, Google AI Overviews) are replacing traditional search for many queries. Unlike SEO where you optimize for ranking position, AEO optimizes for **being the answer** — the source AI models cite, quote, or paraphrase when users ask questions.\n\n## Pre-Publish AEO Checklist\n\nRun through this checklist for every post before publishing:\n\n### Structure for AI Extraction\n- [ ] **Clear Q&A patterns**: Include questions as H2/H3 headings with direct answers in the first sentence of the following paragraph\n- [ ] **FAQ section**: 3-6 questions matching how people ask AI assistants (conversational, natural language)\n- [ ] **Definition paragraphs**: Key concepts defined in 1-2 sentences that AI can extract verbatim\n- [ ] **Comparison tables**: Structured data AI models can parse and cite (at least one per post)\n- [ ] **Numbered lists/steps**: AI models prefer structured, ordered content for \"how to\" queries\n\n### Content Signals\n- [ ] **First-person authority**: Include experience-based statements (\"In our experience...\", \"We tested...\") — AI models weight firsthand expertise\n- [ ] **Specific data points**: Concrete numbers, costs, timeframes — AI models prefer citable facts over vague claims\n- [ ] **Recency signals**: Include dates, \"as of 2026\", current statistics — AI models favor fresh content\n- [ ] **Source citations**: Link to authoritative sources — AI models trust content that references reputable data\n- [ ] **Unique insights**: Include at least one original finding, framework, or data point not available elsewhere\n\n### Brand Consistency\n- [ ] **Consistent terminology**: Use the same branded terms across all posts (e.g., always \"The Always-O
